parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the fuel tank vent rollover valve can cause the fuel tank to collapse, making it difficult to remove the fuel cap, and potentially lead to water ingestion into the fuel system, which can cause engine stalling, poor performance, and increased risk of engine damage.
symptoms: water ingestion into the fuel system
